data.title: Mixed reviews on Mikey V's
data.text: Heard that this was a relative of Vejar family which has a great food place in town. Was mostly disappointed in the food. Chips were obviously from a plastic bag from Smart and Final or some such place. Nothing on menu was anything to talk about. Service was good and staff friendly. Hours are unpredictable. Have tried to go there at times and it was unexpectedly closed.

data.title: Bland Menudo
data.text: Again I returned to Mike V's to try their menudo. Again it was bland tasteless and I probably received 5 pieces of tripe in my overpriced take out. The tortillas that accompanied the menudo were just as bad!

data.title: Menudo with tostitos
data.text: I dined at Mikey V's once only and the menudo was thawed and warmed. It was evident as the tripe had darkened corners and it was tasteless . The tortilla chips served with salsa were tostitos and the salsa was runny.

data.title: Home cooking in ol town, Tulare.
data.text: Very close to my Mother-in-laws cooking style and taste, she treated me to many of her specialties and I have been spoiled. Sadly she is no longer with us, so I have been searching for the taste of love that only she could create in her kitchen. I believe that Mikey V's has her old cooking pot and he's doing it right, here in Tulare, CA.

data.title: Will not be going back
data.text: After hearing so many good this about this little restaurant, I had anticipated nothing less than greatness. I was very disappointed with the bland and watered down meal I ended up with.  The day we are there, they had already "ran out" of various menu items.  Maybe that's why they had added water to the other items to stretch them out. One server was pretty good but several people were also working who seem to have came in off the street and did not know what they were doing. In particular there was one young woman working in pajamas and a sweat shirt.  She was more intent on taking care of a man sitting towards the back, who must have been a boyfriend or even her husband.  She kept taking things to him and running her fingers through his hair and kissing him. Without washing her hands she would occasionally came back and wait on other customers. Food was slow to arrive, with about a five minute gap between the four people I was eating with.  The owners of this restaurant must have another line of work as I cannot see how this place could generate much profit.

data.title: Delicious Mexican Food
data.text: Everything we order tastes great! I especially like their salsa and all of their sauces.  If you like over easy eggs try the New Mexico Enchiladas, you won't regret it! Prices are good and they have fresh fruit for kids. We love this place.

data.title: Good food, friendly service
data.text: We went in and were seated immediately.  As soon as I got the menu, I noticed they were closing in 15 minutes.  I asked them if we should go, but the waitress (and owner, I think) insisted we stay.  The food was good (I had the New Mexico enchiladas - definitely worth trying) and the salsa was tasty.  We offered to pay when we got the food, but again, she said we should just enjoy our meal.  The chef (and owner) came out to settle our bill and thanked us for coming in.  Street parking only - but that wasn't a big deal.  The prices were alright, too.
